ğŸ“¦ Unzipping the GLI Dataset (Simple Steps)

After downloading the GLI dataset, the files come as ZIP files.
We need to open (unzip) them so we can use the data for training.

ğŸ§  What is unzipping? (ELI5)

A ZIP file is like a closed box.
Unzipping means opening the box and taking the files out.

1ï¸âƒ£ Go to the GLI folder on the server
cd ~/sjaipurkar/data/GLI


Check what is inside:

ls -lh


You should see:

ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-TrainingData.zip
ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-ValidationData.zip

2ï¸âƒ£ Create folders for extracted data

This keeps things neat and organized.

mkdir -p training validation

3ï¸âƒ£ Unzip the training dataset
unzip ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-TrainingData.zip -d training


â³ This may take some time because the file is large.

4ï¸âƒ£ Unzip the validation dataset
unzip ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-ValidationData.zip -d validation

5ï¸âƒ£ Check that unzipping worked
ls -lh


Then check inside training:

ls training


You should see a folder like:

ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-TrainingData

6ï¸âƒ£ Check one sample (optional sanity check)
cd training/ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-TrainingData
ls | head


Each folder represents one patient, and inside are MRI files (.nii.gz).

7ï¸âƒ£ (Optional) Delete ZIP files to save space

âš ï¸ Only do this after confirming unzipping worked.

rm ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-TrainingData.zip
rm ASNR-MICCAI-BraTS2023-GLI-Challenge-ValidationData.zip

